rejected a claim to privilege and confidentiality involving a confession of
murder made to a pastor and
counsellor].<br><a name="fn148" href="#fnB148">[145]</a><i> Marriage Act
1955</i> (NZ) s 8; These bodies are the Baptists, Anglican Church,
Congregational Independents, Greek Orthodox, all Hebrew congregations,
Lutheran
churches, Methodists, Presbyterian Church, Roman Catholics, Salvation Army.
Other organisations permitted to nominate celebrants
may apply to the
Registrar-General to be included in the list of approved bodies. To be included
the objects of the organisation
must be primarily to uphold or promote religious
beliefs or philosophical or humanitarian convictions: <i>Marriage Act 1955</i>
(NZ) s 9.<br><a name="fn149" href="#fnB149">[146]</a> New Zealand Acts:<i>
